method.name: count
method.shortdesc: Displays the number of elements in the TimingList.

method.name: add
method.shortdesc: Adds a new event-triggered timing list object.

parameter.name: withProperties
parameter.shortdesc: Initial values for properties of the new TimingList &#40;Optional)

method.name: item
method.shortdesc: Returns the TimingList with the specified index or name.

parameter.name: index
parameter.shortdesc: The index or name. Can accept: Long Integer or String.

method.name: itemByRange
method.shortdesc: Returns the TimingLists within the specified range.

parameter.name: from
parameter.shortdesc: The TimingList, index, or name at the beginning of the range. Can accept: TimingList, Long Integer or String.

parameter.name: to
parameter.shortdesc: The TimingList, index, or name at the end of the range. Can accept: TimingList, Long Integer or String.

method.name: firstItem
method.shortdesc: Returns the first TimingList in the collection.

method.name: lastItem
method.shortdesc: Returns the last TimingList in the collection.

method.name: middleItem
method.shortdesc: Returns the middle TimingList in the collection.

method.name: previousItem
method.shortdesc: Returns the TimingList with the index previous to the specified index.

parameter.name: obj
parameter.shortdesc: The index of the TimingList that follows the desired TimingList.

method.name: nextItem
method.shortdesc: Returns the TimingList whose index follows the specified TimingList in the collection.

parameter.name: obj
parameter.shortdesc: The TimingList whose index comes before the desired TimingList.

method.name: anyItem
method.shortdesc: Returns any TimingList in the collection.

method.name: everyItem
method.shortdesc: Returns every TimingList in the collection.

method.name: toSource
method.shortdesc: Generates a string which, if executed, will return the TimingList.
Returns the TimingList with the specified index.
